KEYWORD: Sexual Behavior and Criminal Conduct

DIGEST: Applicant failed to mitigate the sexual behavior and criminal conduct security concerns. Applicant sexually abused his step-daughter in 2016. He completed extensive sex-offender treatment and was successfully rehabilitated. However, he remains on deferred probation for a felony offense, is subject to restrictions on his lifestyle including regular home searches and blood and urine tests, must avoid certain places and people, and is prohibited from using the internet. His probation period ends in 2024. He failed to report his arrest to his employer for almost one year, and abused the trust given to him by the victim and her mother. Eligibility for access to classified information is denied.

